## Docker Installation

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install ca-certificates curl gnupg -y
sudo install -m 0755 -d /etc/apt/keyrings
curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg
sudo chmod a+r /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg
echo "deb [arch=amd64 signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu noble stable" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-buildx-plugin docker-compose-plugin -y
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
newgrp docker
```

## Required Directories

Create these before running Docker Compose:

```bash
mkdir -p ~/docker-compose/cortex/logs
touch ~/docker-compose/cortex/application.conf
mkdir -p ~/docker-compose/server-configs
mkdir -p ~/docker-compose/logs
mkdir -p ~/docker-compose/files
mkdir -p ~/docker-compose/ssl
```

## Docker Compose File

Place `docker-compose.yml` inside `~/docker-compose/`.

Key configuration decisions:
- Cortex and MISP containers are named with `.local` suffix so TheHive GUI accepts them as FQDNs during integration
- TheHive connects to MinIO via internal Docker network on port 9000 — only the MinIO console (9002) is exposed externally
- Cortex shares the host Docker socket to launch analyzer containers on the host
- All services communicate through the SOC_NET bridge network

### Notable Fixes Applied to Original Tutorial File

| Item | Original | Fixed |
|------|----------|-------|
| MinIO S3 endpoint | http://minio:9002 (console port) | http://minio:9000 (S3 API port) |
| MySQL version | mysql/mysql-server:5.7 (EOL) | mysql:8.0 |
| MySQL auth | default (breaks with MISP) | native password plugin added |
| MISP HOSTNAME | https://10.0.2.10 (wrong IP) | https://10.200.200.253 |
| MISP_BASEURL | localhost | https://10.200.200.253 |
| Timezone | Europe/London | Asia/Riyadh |
| Compose version field | version: "3.7" (deprecated) | removed |

## Deployment

```bash
cd ~/docker-compose
docker compose up -d
```

Verify all containers are running:

```bash
docker compose ps
docker stats --no-stream
```

## Service Startup Times

These services take time to initialize on first run — do not judge availability by browser until these times have passed:

| Service | Expected Startup Time |
|---------|----------------------|
| Cassandra | 1-2 minutes |
| Elasticsearch | 1-2 minutes |
| TheHive | Up to 10 minutes (waits for Cassandra and ES) |
| MISP | 2-3 minutes |
| Cortex | 1-2 minutes |

## Key Lessons

- Cortex and MISP container names must use FQDN format (appending .local) for TheHive GUI integration to accept them
- MinIO exposes two ports — port 9000 for the S3 API (internal only) and port 9002 for the web console. TheHive must connect to port 9000, not 9002
- MySQL 5.7 reached end-of-life in October 2023 — always use MySQL 8.0 with the native password plugin for MISP compatibility
- Always validate docker-compose.yml with python3 before running to catch syntax errors early
- Cassandra and Elasticsearch must be fully initialized before TheHive becomes available — patience is required on first boot
